We introduce CoBloP, a collaborative programming framework with culturally responsive design for ESL and migrant learners, supporting co-located teamwork, cross-device participation, and extensible plug-in games. In a pilot study with 35 middle-school students, many from migrant backgrounds, we observed strong engagement and rapid progression from sequencing to loops and procedures, suggesting CoBloP effectively lowers entry barriers and supports early computational thinking for underserved learners.